§2 In pr. the substitutus is said to become heir to the child: earlier he seems rather to have been regarded as successor to the father, ‘si mihi filius gignitur, isque prius moritur [quam in suam tutelam veniat, sc.] tum ut mihi ille sit heres’ Cic. de orat. 2. 32, ‘non filio, sed sibi’ de invent. 2. 213 cf. Dig. 37. 11. 8. 1.
